SOLuRION:


üõ°Ô∏è Enabling Termination Protection for EC2 Instance
üìñ Lab Explanation
We're enabling Termination Protection for an existing EC2 instance (devops-ec2). This is the exact same concept as Day 8, but now applying it to a different instance. Termination protection prevents accidental stopping or termination of critical instances.

üîç Quick Recap: Key Terms
Termination Protection
What: Safety feature preventing accidental stop/termination

Also Called: Stop Protection (same feature)

AWS Term: "Disable API termination" attribute

üöÄ Why This Matters
Human Error Prevention: Stops accidental "oops" moments

Production Safety: Critical for live systems

Change Control: Enforces proper change procedures

üõ†Ô∏è Step-by-Step Solution
Method: AWS Management Console
Login to AWS Console

bash
# Use the provided credentials:
URL: https://903068777644.signin.aws.amazon.com/console?region=us-east-1
Username: kk_labs_user_152580
Password: SW5X!AVi7jEx
Region: us-east-1 (VERIFY THIS!)
Navigate to EC2 Dashboard

Go to Services ‚Üí EC2

In left sidebar, click "Instances"

Locate the Instance

Find instance named devops-ec2

Use search/filter if needed

Verify region is us-east-1

Enable Termination Protection

Select the devops-ec2 instance

Click Actions ‚Üí Instance settings ‚Üí Change termination protection

Check "Enable"

Click "Save"

Verify Protection

Select the instance

Check Details tab

Termination protection: Should show Enabled

üìã What We Configured
Instance: devops-ec2

Feature: Termination Protection Enabled

Effect: Cannot be stopped or terminated without disabling first

üîß Quick CLI Method
bash
# One-liner to enable protection
aws ec2 modify-instance-attribute \
  --instance-id $(aws ec2 describe-instances \
    --filters "Name=tag:Name,Values=devops-ec2" \
    --query "Reservations[0].Instances[0].InstanceId" \
    --output text) \
  --disable-api-termination "{\"Value\": true}"
‚ö†Ô∏è Important Reminders
Not Foolproof: Authorized users can still disable it

Charges Continue: Instance still incurs costs

Backup Still Needed: Protection ‚â† backup strategy

‚úÖ Verification Steps
Try to stop instance ‚Üí Should fail with error

Try to terminate instance ‚Üí Should fail with error

Both require disabling protection first

üéâ Done!
Termination protection is now enabled for devops-ec2. This instance is now protected from accidental shutdowns or deletions.


